{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781715093634,"sessionID":"ses_1298e5ed2ffeaekxa42UqD0CQE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_9cba512461a0468884c5b5ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-c/workspaces/arm-f5-d4258595/README.md","content":"# Temperature Conversion Library  \n\nA simple Python library for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.  \n\n## Usage  \n\n### CLI Tool  \nRun the command-line interface with:  \n```bash\npython cli.py --from <UNIT> --to <UNIT> <VALUE>\n```  \n\n**Examples:**  \n```bash\npython cli.py --from celsius --to fahrenheit 100\npython cli.py --fahrenheit --to celsius 212\npython cli.py --from celsius --to kelvin 0\n```  \n\n### Supported Units  \n- `celsius` (°C)  \n- `fahrenheit` (°F)  \n- `kelvin` (K)  \n\n## Testing  \nRun tests with `pytest`:  \n```bash\npytest test_converters.py test_cli.py\n```  \n\nEnsure all test cases pass, including edge cases for invalid units and missing arguments."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-c/workspaces/arm-f5-d4258595/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-c/workspaces/arm-f5-d4258595/README.md","time":{"start":1781715093628,"end":1781715093632}},"id":"prt_ed67ec876001HBUDprZqR8LJUE","sessionID":"ses_1298e5ed2ffeaekxa42UqD0CQE","messageID":"msg_ed67d93b9001L7005o5i9cgWpL"}}
